               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Tarikh-i Bukhara, sometimes called Akhbar-i Bukhara andTawarikh i Narshakhi by Narshakhī, Abū Bakr Muḥammad ibn Jaʻfar, 899-959
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_159_1-item1">
                     <author key="person_10789848" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/10789848">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied">Narshakhī, Abū Bakr Muḥammad ibn Jaʻfar, 899-959</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_9533">Tarikh-i Bukhara, sometimes called Akhbar-i Bukhara andTawarikh i Narshakhi.</title>
                     <note>The original author was Abu Bakr Muhammad b. Ja'far Narshakhi Inside front cover: a note in Persian stating that the original title of the work is Tawarikh-i Narshakhi. Folio one, recto, note in Persian giving the price as thirty tankas Folio one, verso, above text: A history and account of the city &amp; holy men of the city of Bochara - purchased at Bochara a translation from the Arabick. A S? W? Burnes Bochara 20th July 1832 Pencilled marginal notes, probably in the hand of Burnes. The two items in the MS are foliated separately. A history and description of Bukhara from its origin to the middle of the tenth century. A Persian version of the Arabic work of Narshakhi, by Muhammad b. [Zafar b] 'Umar, an abridgement of the earlier abridged translation of Abu Nasr Ahmad b. Muhammad al-Qubawi.</note>
                     <incipit>Al-hamdu lillah aladhi bi-ni'mat[ihi tatimma] al-salihat, Sipas u sitayish</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, i, pp. 369-70.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Rieu, Supplement No 87.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
